Pre-heat your oven to 220 degrees. Peel and chop the @sweet potato{1}(peeled and chopped into 2cm cubes) into 2cm cubes. Spread evenly on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and add a pinch of @salt{}. Put in your oven to roast for ~{20%minutes} or until crisp around the edges.

Remove the core from the @green pepper{1}(chopped in half lengthways) and chop it in half lengthways. Chop each half into 1cm strips, then turn them widthways to chop into 1cm cubes. Peel and chop the @carrot{1}(peeled and chopped in half lengthways) in half lengthways, then chop each half into ½cm strips. Turn widthways and chop into ½cm cubes. Peel and slice the @onion{1}(sliced in half lengthways) in half lengthways, then thinly slice widthways (into half moons). Finely chop the @red chilli{1}(finely chopped).

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add your pepper and carrot and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Remove and put on a #plate{} for later.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat. Once the pan is nice and hot (the oil will become thinner and move in the pan like water), add in the @British beef mince{250%g}, spread it evenly, then leave it for ~{2%minutes} without stirring. Turn it over and cook for another ~{2%minutes} without stirring.

> Tip: By leaving the beef alone it'll have a chance to really brown on the outside, improving the taste and the texture.

Add your onion and chilli (less if you don't like spice!) to your pan when your beef is almost cooked. Turn the heat to medium and fry for ~{3%minutes} or until your onion is soft.

Add the @Mexican spice{1.5%tbsp}, a large pinch of @salt{}, a grind of @pepper{} and the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} along with your pepper and carrot. Fill the tin a third with water, swirl it around and add to the pan. Allow to simmer and thicken.

Once your beef mixture has thickened, pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Top with your roasted sweet potato and torn @mozzarella{1}(torn). Bake in your oven until your cheese has melted.

When golden, serve with a dollop of @sour cream{1/2} and get stuck in!